review_blob: Standard beer. Have had this all over. Nice go to beer when better beer isnt available.

review_blob: Bottle. Dark reddish brown with thin brown head. Flavor is moderately sweet. Hints of cocoa, caramel, woody cedar. Slightly nutty. Overall good.

review_blob: On tap at CCB. Aroma of citrus and spice. Has a golden-ish look to it. Fairly light beer. Ok taste.

review_blob: Had on draft at CCB. Nice mixture of bourbons, vanilla, and caramel. Nice, soft finish. Very good.

review_blob: Had this at St. Andrews Pub in NYC. Awesome beer. Great flavor. Can definitely pick up a fruity aroma/taste.
